Opium is bad indeed.

257
00:11:51,030 --> 00:11:52,440
But I

258
00:11:53,790 --> 00:11:56,200
have been addicted to it.

259
00:11:56,590 --> 00:11:59,110
I heard foreign doctors might have a way to quit it.

260
00:11:59,520 --> 00:12:00,880
Would you have a try?

261
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:05,670
My addition

262
00:12:05,670 --> 00:12:08,520
is deep into bones marrows.

263
00:12:09,230 --> 00:12:10,590
If I want to quit,

264
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:13,320
my bones must be broken.

265
00:12:15,880 --> 00:12:17,030
Mr. Hou.

266
00:12:18,150 --> 00:12:21,080
I have something to ask you.

267
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:23,030
You want to ask Fujin,

268
00:12:23,910 --> 00:12:25,030
right?

269
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:30,910
I’ll go to your home tomorrow.

270
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:32,910
Prepare opium for me.

271
00:12:55,640 --> 00:12:56,440
Sister.

272
00:12:57,440 --> 00:12:58,880
Haven’t you gone to sleep?

273
00:13:01,640 --> 00:13:03,110
I did something wrong.

274
00:13:06,790 --> 00:13:07,790
I shouldn’t

275
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:11,230
have allowed you to do arms business with Cao.

276
00:13:12,440 --> 00:13:15,110
You’ve made a fortune by doing business with Fan.

277
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:18,710
I pushed you to this end step by step.

278
00:13:19,280 --> 00:13:20,280
Fengtai.

279
00:13:20,760 --> 00:13:22,280
I made you to this end.

280
00:13:26,590 --> 00:13:27,790
I’m an adult.

281
00:13:27,790 --> 00:13:29,080
I’m not forced by you.

282
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:31,470
It’s my own decision.

283
00:13:32,590 --> 00:13:34,150
Why did you say

284
00:13:34,590 --> 00:13:36,200
those words?

285
00:13:42,760 --> 00:13:44,320
What Cao Guixiu said

286
00:13:46,150 --> 00:13:47,760
is probably true.

287
00:13:51,030 --> 00:13:52,400
What have you seen?

288
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:56,470
Commander has

289
00:13:58,880 --> 00:14:00,350
a Japanese doctor on his side.

290
00:14:07,910 --> 00:14:09,400
Are you sure it’s Japanese?

291
00:14:09,550 --> 00:14:11,640
Commander said it himself.

292
00:14:12,840 --> 00:14:14,110
What should we do?

293
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:16,200
If Commander...

294
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:17,590
Rest assured.

295
00:14:18,280 --> 00:14:20,400
You have me. Take it easy.

296
00:14:20,590 --> 00:14:22,030
It’s useless.

297
00:14:22,440 --> 00:14:24,150
If... If it’s true,

298
00:14:24,640 --> 00:14:26,790
you will also be condemned by people.

299
00:14:27,280 --> 00:14:29,200
I know you care about me.

300
00:14:30,230 --> 00:14:32,590
Don’t scare yourself. Alright?

301
00:14:32,670 --> 00:14:34,080
I’ll figure it out tomorrow.

302
00:14:34,590 --> 00:14:36,230
What you should do now

303
00:14:36,350 --> 00:14:37,440
is to stop drinking.

304
00:14:37,760 --> 00:14:38,590
Take a good rest.

305
00:14:40,230 --> 00:14:41,590
Promise me and I’ll leave.

306
00:14:50,150 --> 00:14:51,000
Goodnight.

307
00:15:16,230 --> 00:15:17,320
This matter

308
00:15:18,670 --> 00:15:21,400
happened 40 years ago.

309
00:15:25,520 --> 00:15:27,520
The emperor was still young.

310
00:15:29,030 --> 00:15:31,440
I,

311
00:15:31,440 --> 00:15:32,440
your father Shang Juzhen,

312
00:15:33,440 --> 00:15:34,640
and Jiang Rongshou

313
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:38,150
welcomed His Majesty at the royal theater.

314
00:15:38,960 --> 00:15:41,110
The opera I performed with Ning Jiulang

315
00:15:41,910 --> 00:15:44,520
was exactly the Search and Rescue of Orphan.

316
00:15:50,960 --> 00:15:51,640
Don’t do this.

317
00:15:51,640 --> 00:15:53,110
I can’t afford it.

318
00:15:53,550 --> 00:15:55,150
His Majesty left palace to avoid to be seen.

319
00:15:55,880 --> 00:15:57,150
He’ll come back once the opera ends.

320
00:15:57,960 --> 00:15:59,150
People walk around.

321
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:00,440
If it is seen,

322
00:16:00,440 --> 00:16:01,590
I will be doomed.

323
00:16:02,710 --> 00:16:03,790
No more nonsense.

324
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:05,710
Fujin An, listen to the edict:

325
00:16:11,640 --> 00:16:12,320
Yes,

326
00:16:13,760 --> 00:16:14,590
I’m listening.

327
00:16:18,520 --> 00:16:19,790
Oral edict from His Majesty.

328
00:16:20,030 --> 00:16:21,470
Fujin is pregnant.

329
00:16:22,110 --> 00:16:23,200
If it’s a boy,

330
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:24,400
he shall be the crown prince.

331
00:16:25,150 --> 00:16:27,320
Lord An and you shall bring him up well

332
00:16:27,710 --> 00:16:31,080
to be the heir of the throne in the future.

333
00:16:31,470 --> 00:16:32,350
Hereby.

334
00:16:32,590 --> 00:16:35,150
His Majesty orders the Save and Rescue of Orphan.

335
00:16:35,150 --> 00:16:37,550
Hou Yukui, Ning Jiulang. Get prepared.

336
00:16:40,260 --> 00:16:56,140
♫Darling, don’t be mad♫

337
00:16:57,580 --> 00:17:03,460
♫Let me explain to you♫

338
00:17:10,060 --> 00:17:10,430
♫Zhao family and Tu family have a grudge♫

339
00:17:10,430 --> 00:17:13,760
Only then did I know those two women were
♫Zhao family and Tu family have a grudge♫

340
00:17:13,760 --> 00:17:16,589
Empress Zhen and Fujin.
♫Zhao family and Tu family have a grudge♫

341
00:17:16,589 --> 00:17:17,380
♫Zhao family and Tu family have a grudge♫

342
00:17:18,430 --> 00:17:19,710
Later,

343
00:17:22,430 --> 00:17:25,560
Fujin did give birth to a boy,

344
00:17:26,190 --> 00:17:28,400
and taught him reading,

345
00:17:28,760 --> 00:17:30,400
horse riding and archery.

346
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:31,830
Badly,

347
00:17:33,110 --> 00:17:36,640
Peking was wrecked by the Revolution in 1911.

348
00:17:38,950 --> 00:17:42,110
The little boy went out and played alone,

349
00:17:43,950 --> 00:17:46,950
and didn’t come back again.

350
00:17:48,560 --> 00:17:50,520
His Majesty meant to entrust Lord An

351
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:54,350
by the opera Search and Rescue Orphan.

352
00:17:55,640 --> 00:18:00,470
That became a sore point to Fujin.

353
00:18:02,430 --> 00:18:03,430
No wonder.

354
00:18:05,640 --> 00:18:07,400
If she raised the boy,

355
00:18:08,470 --> 00:18:10,400
she would fail Empress Dowager.

356
00:18:11,430 --> 00:18:13,070
But she lost the boy,

357
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:15,880
and failed His Majesty and Empress Zhenfei.

358
00:18:17,280 --> 00:18:18,800
At last,

359
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:22,760
she got crazy.

360
00:18:23,190 --> 00:18:31,880
It’s pathetic. Pathetic.

361
00:18:35,800 --> 00:18:37,920
The emperor got in danger.

362
00:18:39,310 --> 00:18:41,400
Zhen risked her life to tell the edict.

363
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:44,310
Fujin was in dilemma due to loyalty.

364
00:18:45,880 --> 00:18:47,760
It is a touching story.

365
00:18:49,830 --> 00:18:50,640
Mr. Hou.

366
00:18:51,310 --> 00:18:52,470
I want to adapt it into opera.

367
00:18:52,470 --> 00:18:53,520
What do you think?

368
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:57,470
Ridiculous.

369
00:18:58,110 --> 00:18:59,760
I tell the royal secrets.

370
00:19:00,560 --> 00:19:02,470
How dare you adapt it into opera?

371
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:18,590
You have a point.

372
00:19:19,760 --> 00:19:22,830
Operas are all from secrets,

373
00:19:22,830 --> 00:19:24,230
privacy,

374
00:19:24,230 --> 00:19:26,070
or rumors in history.

375
00:19:27,070 --> 00:19:29,040
Mr. Hou. if you’re willing to

376
00:19:29,280 --> 00:19:30,590
play the emperor in this play,

377
00:19:30,880 --> 00:19:32,760
that will be great.

378
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:35,230
Give you an inch and you’ll take an ell.

379
00:19:36,920 --> 00:19:38,590
If it were thirty years ago,

380
00:19:38,590 --> 00:19:39,920
I would agree.

381
00:19:42,560 --> 00:19:44,310
Not anymore.

382
00:19:59,280 --> 00:20:01,880
The theater in Lord An’s mansion

383
00:20:03,350 --> 00:20:05,880
is a good place.

384
00:20:06,950 --> 00:20:09,040
When you stand there,

385
00:20:10,680 --> 00:20:12,590
you will feel at home.

386
00:20:13,950 --> 00:20:15,590
But it is ostentatious,

387
00:20:16,880 --> 00:20:20,470
not all performers are able to act there.

388
00:20:33,160 --> 00:20:35,160
If you want to go there,

389
00:20:36,520 --> 00:20:38,110
I’ll talk to Fujin

390
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:41,070
with Ning Jiulang.

391
00:20:41,400 --> 00:20:42,640
She may agree.

392
00:20:42,880 --> 00:20:45,560
I want to. I do want to.

393
00:20:46,190 --> 00:20:47,400
Thanks, Mr. Hou.

394
00:20:51,070 --> 00:20:51,800
I won’t write.

395
00:20:53,950 --> 00:20:55,190
Why not?

396
00:20:55,190 --> 00:20:56,400
It’s a good story.

397
00:20:57,680 --> 00:20:59,160
My father served His Majesty back then.

398
00:20:59,430 --> 00:21:01,310
I know the things in emperor's family well.

399
00:21:01,560 --> 00:21:03,350
The year and date are all wrong.

400
00:21:03,680 --> 00:21:05,680
Is Hou Yukui confused by opium?

401
00:21:05,680 --> 00:21:06,710
Did he make fun of you?

402
00:21:06,710 --> 00:21:08,310
Whether true or not,

403
00:21:08,310 --> 00:21:09,880
the story is interesting, isn't it?

404
00:21:09,880 --> 00:21:11,710
I don’t care if it’s interesting.

405
00:21:11,950 --> 00:21:13,880
I won’t write based on the nonsense.

406
00:21:13,880 --> 00:21:16,830
Even nonsense is better than fabricated stories.

407
00:21:21,040 --> 00:21:22,040
What did you say?

408
00:21:23,310 --> 00:21:23,950
You like it?

409
00:21:24,560 --> 00:21:25,640
I'll tell you again.

410
00:21:26,070 --> 00:21:27,710
Even nonsense

411
00:21:27,710 --> 00:21:30,430
is better than your fabricated stories.

412
00:21:35,640 --> 00:21:36,070
Fine.

413
00:21:37,680 --> 00:21:38,430
Good.

414
00:21:39,920 --> 00:21:40,640
Alright.

415
00:21:41,520 --> 00:21:42,310
Mr. Du.

416
00:21:50,560 --> 00:21:51,920
What’s wrong him?

417
00:21:52,710 --> 00:21:53,590
Ignore him.

418
00:21:53,590 --> 00:21:54,560
Literati’s common problem.

419
00:21:54,710 --> 00:21:55,800
He deserves to be scolded.

420
00:21:58,040 --> 00:21:59,950
You often quarrel for new operas.

421
00:22:01,040 --> 00:22:02,430
Starof Wisdom

422
00:22:02,430 --> 00:22:04,190
will leave you sooner or later.

423
00:22:04,190 --> 00:22:05,110
He won’t.

424
00:22:05,430 --> 00:22:07,830
He will be back in a few days.

425
00:22:08,280 --> 00:22:09,430
You know why?

426
00:22:13,950 --> 00:22:16,310
He has a high taste.

427
00:22:16,710 --> 00:22:18,070
He looks down on others

428
00:22:18,070 --> 00:22:19,560
except me.

429
00:22:25,710 --> 00:22:26,560
You were absent-minded

430
00:22:26,560 --> 00:22:27,880
when I talked to you.

431
00:22:27,950 --> 00:22:28,830
What brings you here?

432
00:22:31,110 --> 00:22:32,310
I have something on my mind.

433
00:22:38,400 --> 00:22:39,920
You have something on your mind?

434
00:22:40,190 --> 00:22:41,950
Can’t I have something on my mind?

435
00:22:46,560 --> 00:22:49,190
You usually look wise

436
00:22:49,310 --> 00:22:51,160
and insightful.

437
00:22:52,430 --> 00:22:53,880
How come you have something on your mind?

438
00:22:54,800 --> 00:22:56,400
Tell me. What is it?

439
00:22:58,640 --> 00:23:00,160
Many people say that

440
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:02,430
someone does something wrong.

441
00:23:05,160 --> 00:23:06,880
I don’t know if it’s true.

442
00:23:07,950 --> 00:23:09,680
I don’t know how to prove it.

443
00:23:11,560 --> 00:23:12,710
Go and ask.

444
00:23:12,920 --> 00:23:13,880
Ask whom?

445
00:23:14,310 --> 00:23:15,520
Ask him.

446
00:23:16,110 --> 00:23:18,800
Hey. He knows the best

447
00:23:18,950 --> 00:23:20,800
if he has done something wrong.

448
00:23:21,310 --> 00:23:21,950
Ask him

449
00:23:22,110 --> 00:23:23,160
and see how he explains.

450
00:23:23,950 --> 00:23:24,830
Don’t

451
00:23:24,830 --> 00:23:26,190
ponder it here alone.

452
00:23:26,430 --> 00:23:28,190
Prove? How to prove?

453
00:23:28,190 --> 00:23:29,920
You won’t be worried if you can prove it here.

454
00:23:30,880 --> 00:23:32,000
You’re right.

455
00:23:33,920 --> 00:23:35,160
You have a point.

456
00:23:37,520 --> 00:23:38,160
I’m leaving.

457
00:23:40,070 --> 00:23:41,640
A big fool.

458
00:23:44,950 --> 00:23:46,310
Brazilian tobacco.

459
00:23:47,520 --> 00:23:48,800
Take it back and try it.

460
00:23:52,640 --> 00:23:53,760
It’s good.

461
00:23:57,760 --> 00:23:59,560
Your sister asked you to come?

462
00:24:01,640 --> 00:24:03,190
She is moody

463
00:24:03,190 --> 00:24:03,920
and jealous.

464
00:24:04,680 --> 00:24:07,680
You’re a man. Don’t take it seriously.

465
00:24:13,350 --> 00:24:14,350
Cao.

466
00:24:16,470 --> 00:24:19,880
It’s said you’re close to Japanese. Is it true?

467
00:24:27,950 --> 00:24:29,400
Who told you this?

468
00:24:31,110 --> 00:24:32,000
Call him here.

469
00:24:32,310 --> 00:24:33,400
I’ll shoot him.

470
00:24:36,760 --> 00:24:37,430
Cao.

471
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:40,400
Is it true?

472
00:24:43,070 --> 00:24:44,520
You’re a businessman.

473
00:24:44,760 --> 00:24:46,590
Don’t get involved in it.

474
00:24:47,310 --> 00:24:48,520
Just take good care of

475
00:24:48,520 --> 00:24:50,760
your own business.

476
00:24:51,800 --> 00:24:53,800
Don’t believe the rumor.

477
00:24:53,880 --> 00:24:55,830
That’s no ordinary rumor.

478
00:24:57,110 --> 00:24:58,280
I deliver goods for you.

479
00:24:59,310 --> 00:25:01,160
If you’re close to Japanese,

480
00:25:01,680 --> 00:25:04,000
the whole Cheng family will be implicated.

481
00:25:05,070 --> 00:25:06,040
Commander.

482
00:25:07,520 --> 00:25:08,950
I don’t want to be a traitor.

483
00:25:14,040 --> 00:25:15,640
What are you talking about?

484
00:25:17,950 --> 00:25:19,110
I mean I...

485
00:25:19,710 --> 00:25:20,470
Who is it?

486
00:25:21,070 --> 00:25:22,880
I’m Kimura.

487
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:29,190
Come in.

488
00:25:31,520 --> 00:25:33,230
Cheng family is nothing.

489
00:25:36,230 --> 00:25:37,350
I, Cao Wanjun,

490
00:25:37,430 --> 00:25:39,520
are not able to protect your family?

491
00:25:40,190 --> 00:25:42,040
Just deliver the goods to the destination.

492
00:25:42,430 --> 00:25:43,160
That’s all.

493
00:25:44,160 --> 00:25:45,760
Don’t ask more.

494
00:25:46,230 --> 00:25:47,040
Scram.

495
00:25:57,070 --> 00:25:59,070
Look. He dares to question me.

496
00:26:17,800 --> 00:26:19,950
Mr. Cheng. You ask for me?

497
00:26:20,880 --> 00:26:22,830
Are Commander’s goods delivered?

498
00:26:23,070 --> 00:26:23,640
Not yet.

499
00:26:24,230 --> 00:26:26,310
By train at 10 p.m.

500
00:26:27,710 --> 00:26:28,310
Don't deliver them.

501
00:26:29,470 --> 00:26:30,400
Leave them there.

502
00:26:31,520 --> 00:26:32,230
But...

503
00:26:33,400 --> 00:26:34,470
Is it OK?

504
00:26:34,800 --> 00:26:36,560
He has been urging us.

505
00:26:37,190 --> 00:26:38,040
Leave it aside.

506
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:39,830
That’s it.

507
00:26:41,920 --> 00:26:43,280
Yes, Mr. Cheng.

508
00:27:15,590 --> 00:27:18,000
Mr. Du, you treat me to meal

509
00:27:18,430 --> 00:27:20,830
or you let me accompany for drinking?

510
00:27:21,110 --> 00:27:22,280
What's wrong?

511
00:27:23,880 --> 00:27:25,190
Wine and dishes here.

512
00:27:25,520 --> 00:27:26,830
You don’t like them?

513
00:27:29,640 --> 00:27:31,110
Who offended you?

514
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:36,950
Shang Xirui?

515
00:27:36,950 --> 00:27:38,040
Don’t bring him up.

516
00:27:40,470 --> 00:27:41,880
Bastard.

517
00:27:42,830 --> 00:27:44,000
Let me tell you.

518
00:27:44,000 --> 00:27:45,640
From today on,

519
00:27:45,800 --> 00:27:48,520
I, Du Luocheng, has nothing to do

520
00:27:48,520 --> 00:27:50,950
with Shang Xirui. Understand?

521
00:27:51,430 --> 00:27:52,470
It means

522
00:27:53,070 --> 00:27:56,160
you won't write scripts for him?

523
00:27:56,160 --> 00:27:57,800
Bastards write for him.

524
00:28:01,710 --> 00:28:02,230
Fine.

525
00:28:03,040 --> 00:28:05,190
Don't write for him then.

526
00:28:06,470 --> 00:28:08,160
Come. Come.

527
00:28:08,160 --> 00:28:09,400
Let me fill your cup.

528
00:28:09,920 --> 00:28:11,920
So many troupes in Peking.

529
00:28:12,430 --> 00:28:14,280
And you are well-known.

530
00:28:14,800 --> 00:28:16,110
Many performers

531
00:28:16,110 --> 00:28:18,560
will take money and beg you to write scripts.

532
00:28:18,560 --> 00:28:20,310
Right? Here.

533
00:28:23,680 --> 00:28:24,470
Come on.

534
00:28:25,280 --> 00:28:26,430
Of course.

535
00:28:31,760 --> 00:28:32,880
I heard Jiang Dengbao

536
00:28:32,880 --> 00:28:35,040
of Spring Theater ever asked you to write.

537
00:28:35,520 --> 00:28:36,560
In my opinion,

538
00:28:36,560 --> 00:28:37,590
you’ve written lots of operas for female roles.

539
00:28:37,590 --> 00:28:38,950
You may write males’ stories for Jiang Dengbao.

540
00:28:38,950 --> 00:28:39,880
Save it.

541
00:28:40,400 --> 00:28:41,710
He’s an idiot.

542
00:28:43,950 --> 00:28:45,350
What about Sixi’er of Yunxi Theater?

543
00:28:46,430 --> 00:28:47,640
How old is he?

544
00:28:48,190 --> 00:28:49,560
His performance is

545
00:28:49,560 --> 00:28:51,680
like the spider goblin in the Journey to the West.

546
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:53,350
Chen Renxiang.

547
00:28:53,830 --> 00:28:54,710
How about him?

548
00:28:54,920 --> 00:28:56,000
Write for him

549
00:28:56,280 --> 00:28:57,640
once he comes back from Shanghai.

550
00:29:00,110 --> 00:29:02,040
Him?

551
00:29:02,760 --> 00:29:05,310
He was defeated by Shang Xirui.

552
00:29:05,430 --> 00:29:07,310
Let me write for him?

553
00:29:07,310 --> 00:29:08,470
Nonsense.

554
00:29:10,830 --> 00:29:12,400
You like none of them.

555
00:29:12,710 --> 00:29:15,160
Why are you still scolding Mr. Shang?

556
00:29:17,230 --> 00:29:18,400
Did I scold him?

557
00:29:19,800 --> 00:29:21,760
He is a madman, isn’t he?

558
00:29:21,760 --> 00:29:22,400
Yes. Yes.

559
00:29:22,400 --> 00:29:23,880
Why do I bother meddling with him?

560
00:29:24,680 --> 00:29:25,680
Here. Come on.

561
00:29:26,830 --> 00:29:27,590
No.

562
00:29:29,640 --> 00:29:31,000
Where are you going?

563
00:29:36,400 --> 00:29:37,190
Mr. Du.

564
00:29:39,280 --> 00:29:40,070
Go home

565
00:29:40,560 --> 00:29:41,880
and write scripts.

566
00:29:53,520 --> 00:29:56,520
I accompanied you, but the bill is on me?

567
00:29:57,880 --> 00:30:00,400
Your goods are not ready yet.

568
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:02,760
You come to urge me?

569
00:30:03,230 --> 00:30:05,760
You are cold to me.

570
00:30:06,160 --> 00:30:07,560
Are you in bad mood?

571
00:30:10,470 --> 00:30:12,070
My Cheng family

572
00:30:12,070 --> 00:30:13,830
is unlucky,

573
00:30:14,800 --> 00:30:16,800
always troubled by Cao family.

574
00:30:17,430 --> 00:30:20,160
All of you are troublemakers.

575
00:30:24,520 --> 00:30:25,350
Cheng.

576
00:30:26,230 --> 00:30:28,070
That’s unreasonable.

577
00:30:28,470 --> 00:30:30,000
You don’t deliver goods for me.

578
00:30:30,470 --> 00:30:33,040
So, you should know I don’t side with him.

579
00:30:36,040 --> 00:30:38,190
That’s more troublesome.

580
00:30:39,640 --> 00:30:41,230
I risked my life

581
00:30:41,470 --> 00:30:43,880
not to deliver goods to Commander.

582
00:30:44,710 --> 00:30:47,230
Now I have to deliver your goods behind his back.

583
00:30:47,560 --> 00:30:49,160
If he knows this,

584
00:30:49,470 --> 00:30:52,190
I’ll take two bullets from him.

585
00:30:52,830 --> 00:30:54,950
Men from Shanghai are said to be meticulous

586
00:30:54,950 --> 00:30:56,070
and timid.

587
00:30:56,680 --> 00:30:59,760
I thought you had thought twice before doing that.

588
00:31:00,230 --> 00:31:02,230
Surprisingly, you had nerve

589
00:31:02,640 --> 00:31:05,110
and questioned him face to face.

590
00:31:05,400 --> 00:31:07,920
That’s a bad move.

591
00:31:09,710 --> 00:31:11,920
I stayed long with reckless men lately.

592
00:31:12,040 --> 00:31:13,640
I got bewildered, too.

593
00:31:19,880 --> 00:31:20,760
Uncle.

594
00:31:21,950 --> 00:31:23,070
Don't worry.

595
00:31:23,590 --> 00:31:25,760
I’m here to solve your problem.

596
00:31:27,430 --> 00:31:28,590
How?

597
00:31:28,800 --> 00:31:31,310
Deliver Commander’s goods as usual.

598
00:31:31,520 --> 00:31:33,160
Don’t prepare

599
00:31:33,350 --> 00:31:34,830
my goods.

600
00:31:35,470 --> 00:31:36,560
Just tell me

601
00:31:36,560 --> 00:31:39,880
where his warehouse is in Peking.

602
00:31:46,280 --> 00:31:49,160
You want to loot his goods?

603
00:31:50,310 --> 00:31:52,190
Loot is a bad word.

604
00:31:52,640 --> 00:31:54,560
I’m his son.

605
00:31:54,880 --> 00:31:57,680
They’re still in Cao’s hand.

606
00:31:58,710 --> 00:31:59,640
Right?

607
00:32:06,160 --> 00:32:07,640
I haven't seen Mr. Du for days.

608
00:32:08,280 --> 00:32:09,680
Haven't you made up?

609
00:32:10,040 --> 00:32:10,430
No.

610
00:32:11,310 --> 00:32:12,310
He is writing scripts at home.

611
00:32:14,520 --> 00:32:16,070
Is he willing to write for you?

612
00:32:17,110 --> 00:32:18,520
You’re capable.

613
00:32:18,830 --> 00:32:20,350
You have my admiration.

614
00:32:20,560 --> 00:32:21,640
I’ve told you.

615
00:32:21,640 --> 00:32:22,040
He

616
00:32:22,470 --> 00:32:23,560
wouldn’t leave me.

617
00:32:24,830 --> 00:32:25,950
I have

618
00:32:26,950 --> 00:32:28,950
more good news for you.

619
00:32:29,560 --> 00:32:31,070
Double happiness.

620
00:32:32,230 --> 00:32:33,470
You will be extremely happy

621
00:32:33,560 --> 00:32:35,070
when you hear it.

622
00:32:36,070 --> 00:32:37,230
Take a guess.

623
00:32:38,110 --> 00:32:39,680
I have no idea. Tell me.

624
00:32:42,680 --> 00:32:43,350
Lord An

625
00:32:44,590 --> 00:32:45,400
agreed

626
00:32:46,800 --> 00:32:48,040
to sell his theater

627
00:32:49,110 --> 00:32:50,110
to us.

628
00:32:53,160 --> 00:32:54,310
What did you say?

629
00:33:04,140 --> 00:33:05,340
(Deeds of purchase)

630
00:33:20,110 --> 00:33:21,040
So,

631
00:33:21,950 --> 00:33:23,160
Shuiyun can perform

632
00:33:23,160 --> 00:33:25,590
in the royal theater?

633
00:33:25,590 --> 00:33:26,470
Right.

634
00:33:26,830 --> 00:33:27,710
Shuiyun,

635
00:33:28,310 --> 00:33:29,520
Shang Xirui,

636
00:33:29,920 --> 00:33:34,070
will perform in the royal theater afterwards.

637
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:39,920
Thanks to

638
00:33:40,110 --> 00:33:42,280
Hou Yukui and Ning Jiulang.

639
00:33:42,280 --> 00:33:43,470
They made it possible.

640
00:33:44,280 --> 00:33:46,160
But Lord An has

641
00:33:46,520 --> 00:33:48,280
another condition besides money.

642
00:33:48,680 --> 00:33:51,040
If Shuiyun can move there,

643
00:33:51,190 --> 00:33:53,190
it all depends on your decision.

644
00:33:53,190 --> 00:33:54,800
Not to mention one condition.

645
00:33:55,040 --> 00:33:57,430
If I can buy the royal theater,

646
00:33:57,430 --> 00:33:58,880
I agree to any condition.

647
00:33:58,880 --> 00:33:59,950
Even

648
00:34:00,640 --> 00:34:01,310
you let me

649
00:34:02,920 --> 00:34:04,190
call Jiang Rongshou

650
00:34:04,830 --> 00:34:07,040
the grand master right now.

651
00:34:09,600 --> 00:34:11,280
Lord An won't do that.

652
00:34:11,909 --> 00:34:13,670
Actually, it’s no big deal.

653
00:34:14,080 --> 00:34:15,000
Afterwards,

654
00:34:15,600 --> 00:34:19,000
build a wall between the theater and the garden.

655
00:34:19,280 --> 00:34:21,360
Whenever Fujin wants to watch opera,

656
00:34:21,630 --> 00:34:24,520
you need to go to the mansion and perform for her.

657
00:34:26,710 --> 00:34:27,840
That’s all?

658
00:34:29,230 --> 00:34:30,760
A piece of cake.

659
00:34:31,280 --> 00:34:33,870
Whether Peking Opera or Kun opera,

660
00:34:33,870 --> 00:34:34,870
as long as I have learned,

661
00:34:34,870 --> 00:34:35,429
no,

662
00:34:35,429 --> 00:34:37,120
as long as I can learn,

663
00:34:37,120 --> 00:34:39,080
I will perform whatever she wants.

664
00:34:39,120 --> 00:34:40,560
It's done then.

665
00:34:46,520 --> 00:34:48,150
These two elders

666
00:34:48,389 --> 00:34:50,040
are good at calculating.

667
00:34:50,870 --> 00:34:52,190
The land is sold,

668
00:34:52,320 --> 00:34:54,120
and money is in the pocket.

669
00:34:55,190 --> 00:34:58,470
But the theater can’t be moved away.

670
00:34:58,910 --> 00:35:01,230
The old lady can watch your opera every day.

671
00:35:01,560 --> 00:35:03,390
Even the handsome fee to invite performers

672
00:35:03,710 --> 00:35:06,280
for banquets will be saved in the future.

673
00:35:07,320 --> 00:35:08,630
The royal descendant

674
00:35:09,080 --> 00:35:11,150
is better than me at doing business.

675
00:35:12,600 --> 00:35:14,230
As long as I can buy

676
00:35:14,230 --> 00:35:16,230
this theater which was ever visited by emperor,

677
00:35:16,470 --> 00:35:17,800
I don’t care how much it costs.

678
00:35:18,230 --> 00:35:19,190
Besides,

679
00:35:19,360 --> 00:35:21,360
Fujin knows opera.

680
00:35:21,520 --> 00:35:23,560
I’m willing to perform for her.

681
00:35:24,630 --> 00:35:25,950
The emperor has run away.

682
00:35:26,320 --> 00:35:28,320
It’s useless even if it’s visited by emperor.

683
00:35:30,280 --> 00:35:31,630
You know nothing.

684
00:35:32,670 --> 00:35:33,840
I believe it’s worth.

685
00:35:35,600 --> 00:35:36,670
Fine. Fine.

686
00:35:36,950 --> 00:35:39,150
-Put it away.
-You are absolutely right.

687
00:35:40,390 --> 00:35:41,760
Where are you going?

688
00:35:41,760 --> 00:35:44,080
I... I’m going to pay respects to Fujin.

689
00:35:44,080 --> 00:35:46,040
She sold a good theater to me.

690
00:35:46,230 --> 00:35:47,470
I’m going to thank her.

691
00:35:48,670 --> 00:35:51,000
It’s credulous of you.

692
00:35:54,040 --> 00:35:55,470
Fool.

693
00:37:19,080 --> 00:37:19,870
Bravo!

694
00:37:20,320 --> 00:37:22,390
-Bravo!
-Bravo!

695
00:37:22,520 --> 00:37:28,080
-Bravo!
-Bravo!

696
00:37:29,800 --> 00:37:31,520
-Bravo!
-Bravo!

697
00:37:32,470 --> 00:37:33,390
Bravo!

698
00:37:33,670 --> 00:37:36,950
Today is a big day when the Royal Theater opens.

699
00:37:37,080 --> 00:37:38,760
On behalf of our theater,

700
00:37:38,800 --> 00:37:40,670
I’d like to extend my warm welcome

701
00:37:40,670 --> 00:37:42,280
and heartfelt thanks

702
00:37:42,280 --> 00:37:45,320
to the reporters, and the fans.

703
00:37:45,320 --> 00:37:51,540
Bravo!

704
00:37:51,540 --> 00:37:52,910
(First Theater)
Bravo!

705
00:37:52,910 --> 00:37:55,060
(First Theater)

706
00:38:47,900 --> 00:38:53,180
(The Tale of Dragon)

707
00:38:58,280 --> 00:39:02,230
-Bravo!
-Bravo!

708
00:39:03,670 --> 00:39:08,800
A hero Gongsun

709
00:39:10,520 --> 00:39:18,150
ever wielded a sword and conquered the world.

710
00:39:20,280 --> 00:39:21,600
Is he drunk?

711
00:39:22,150 --> 00:39:23,520
You are amazing, Xirui.

712
00:39:24,560 --> 00:39:25,800
Few can match

713
00:39:26,800 --> 00:39:28,390
your swordsmanship in Peking,

714
00:39:29,360 --> 00:39:31,910
not to mention in Shuiyun Theater.

715
00:39:31,910 --> 00:39:33,910
What’s wrong with you today?

716
00:39:33,910 --> 00:39:35,190
You’re honey-mouthed.

717
00:39:35,760 --> 00:39:37,280
Is the script done?

718
00:39:37,390 --> 00:39:38,280
Yes.

719
00:39:42,280 --> 00:39:43,190
Xirui.

720
00:39:43,800 --> 00:39:45,190
Read it carefully.

721
00:39:47,080 --> 00:39:48,120
My script

722
00:39:48,950 --> 00:39:51,190
is unprecedented,

723
00:39:51,800 --> 00:39:53,320
unparalleled,

724
00:39:54,670 --> 00:39:56,430
and extraordinary.

725
00:39:56,800 --> 00:39:57,800
Excellent.

726
00:39:58,870 --> 00:40:00,360
Stop boasting.

727
00:40:00,360 --> 00:40:01,430
Don't you feel ashamed?

728
00:40:02,320 --> 00:40:03,280
Mr. Cheng. Read it.

729
00:40:04,670 --> 00:40:05,520
Sure.

730
00:40:05,950 --> 00:40:07,430
Serve the star.

731
00:40:08,150 --> 00:40:09,560
Wait a second.

732
00:40:10,150 --> 00:40:12,630
There is a small problem.

733
00:40:12,800 --> 00:40:13,670
What?

734
00:40:14,800 --> 00:40:15,560
The queen

735
00:40:15,560 --> 00:40:16,840
dies in my opera.

736
00:40:16,840 --> 00:40:19,280
The emperor is the leading role.

737
00:40:19,800 --> 00:40:20,360
Hey.

738
00:40:23,520 --> 00:40:25,280
The queen dies.

739
00:40:25,430 --> 00:40:26,630
What should I perform?

740
00:40:26,800 --> 00:40:28,150
How about...

741
00:40:29,430 --> 00:40:30,840
How about you play the emperor?

742
00:40:31,320 --> 00:40:32,040
Well...

743
00:40:32,040 --> 00:40:33,320
Leader plays the emperor?

744
00:40:35,120 --> 00:40:36,150
Mr. Du.

745
00:40:36,520 --> 00:40:38,150
Do you forget my role?

746
00:40:38,520 --> 00:40:40,000
I’ve finished my script.

747
00:40:40,280 --> 00:40:40,950
That’s it.

748
00:40:41,150 --> 00:40:41,800
I can’t help.

749
00:40:41,860 --> 00:40:41,910
(The Tale of Dragon)

750
00:40:41,910 --> 00:40:42,390
Modify it.
(The Tale of Dragon)

751
00:40:42,390 --> 00:40:43,040
(The Tale of Dragon)

752
00:40:43,040 --> 00:40:43,800
Modify it right.
(The Tale of Dragon)

753
00:40:43,910 --> 00:40:45,230
I can’t.

754
00:40:45,470 --> 00:40:48,000
My story is given by Heaven.

755
00:40:48,150 --> 00:40:48,630
You think

756
00:40:48,630 --> 00:40:50,280
it’s fabricated?

757
00:40:50,280 --> 00:40:51,950
Ask God to modify it.

758
00:40:53,600 --> 00:40:55,280
You play the fool with me?

759
00:40:56,150 --> 00:40:57,040
Don’t fight.

760
00:40:57,040 --> 00:40:57,950
Cut it out.

761
00:40:57,950 --> 00:40:59,910
Mr. Du. Leave now.

762
00:40:59,910 --> 00:41:01,280
Let me talk to Mr. Shang.

763
00:41:01,280 --> 00:41:02,280
You let the leading role die?

764
00:41:02,560 --> 00:41:03,800
Ridiculous.

765
00:41:03,800 --> 00:41:04,630
Can you write or not?

766
00:41:04,800 --> 00:41:05,320
Stop.

767
00:41:05,840 --> 00:41:06,670
Cut it out.

768
00:41:06,670 --> 00:41:07,600
He is useless, isn’t he?

769
00:41:07,600 --> 00:41:08,520
Stop yelling.

770
00:41:09,630 --> 00:41:10,520
Stinking temper.

771
00:41:11,470 --> 00:41:11,800
Go.

772
00:41:13,710 --> 00:41:15,520
-Leader.
-Leader.

773
00:41:15,600 --> 00:41:16,560
I can't modify it.

774
00:41:18,870 --> 00:41:20,320
Say no more.

775
00:41:20,320 --> 00:41:21,150
Make way.

776
00:41:21,230 --> 00:41:22,560
Mr. Du. Mr. Du.

777
00:41:24,120 --> 00:41:25,630
How could it be like this?

778
00:41:25,630 --> 00:41:26,600
Right.

779
00:41:42,840 --> 00:41:44,280
Good opera.

780
00:41:46,390 --> 00:41:47,280
Good.

781
00:42:00,910 --> 00:42:02,470
Now I believe what Mr. Du said.

782
00:42:03,470 --> 00:42:04,910
Good stories

783
00:42:05,230 --> 00:42:06,520
are offered by God.

784
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:08,710
It all relies on fate.

785
00:42:09,230 --> 00:42:10,430
Unchangeable.

786
00:42:11,760 --> 00:42:13,080
In a month,

787
00:42:13,360 --> 00:42:15,230
the leader of Peking Opera will be elected.

788
00:42:16,230 --> 00:42:17,870
The emperor in the opera

789
00:42:18,390 --> 00:42:20,040
is brilliant.

790
00:42:20,560 --> 00:42:22,000
You will definitely win

791
00:42:22,190 --> 00:42:23,230
by this.

792
00:42:24,190 --> 00:42:24,670
I decided

793
00:42:25,390 --> 00:42:26,280
to play the emperor.

794
00:42:30,600 --> 00:42:31,520
Who will play the queen then?

795
00:42:46,230 --> 00:42:47,520
Take baby to sleep.

796
00:42:49,190 --> 00:42:50,710
Be good.

797
00:42:54,710 --> 00:42:55,800
Don’t hide it.

798
00:42:56,840 --> 00:42:59,320
Cheng bought the royal theater.

799
00:43:04,150 --> 00:43:05,910
I’m afraid of you two quarreling.

800
00:43:06,470 --> 00:43:08,280
You didn't talk to each other the other day.

801
00:43:08,470 --> 00:43:09,710
That’s enough for me.

802
00:43:10,560 --> 00:43:11,560
We won’t.

803
00:43:12,150 --> 00:43:13,600
I’ve made a deal with him.

804
00:43:13,870 --> 00:43:15,950
He can have fun with the performers,

805
00:43:17,040 --> 00:43:19,910
better than whoring, gamble or taking drug.

806
00:43:22,950 --> 00:43:23,950
How come

807
00:43:24,710 --> 00:43:26,360
he still has fun with performers?

808
00:43:28,520 --> 00:43:30,000
Are you upset in my stead?

809
00:43:33,390 --> 00:43:34,560
I mean

810
00:43:34,560 --> 00:43:36,000
Commander is back,

811
00:43:36,320 --> 00:43:38,080
while he’s still in the theater.

812
00:43:38,280 --> 00:43:39,360
Good-for-nothing.

813
00:43:39,840 --> 00:43:40,840
Commander is back?

814
00:43:41,040 --> 00:43:42,840
Why don’t you keep an eye on him?

815
00:43:44,080 --> 00:43:45,360
It’s too late.

816
00:43:47,390 --> 00:43:48,800
When you came back from the barracks,

817
00:43:49,080 --> 00:43:50,360
you looked weird

818
00:43:50,910 --> 00:43:52,320
and inspirited.

819
00:43:54,190 --> 00:43:55,150
What’s on your mind?

820
00:43:58,120 --> 00:43:58,910
Rest assured.

821
00:43:58,910 --> 00:43:59,670
Nothing.

822
00:44:01,670 --> 00:44:03,430
A wicked woman

823
00:44:04,390 --> 00:44:05,870
came to the barracks.

824
00:44:06,710 --> 00:44:08,320
I quarreled with the Commander.

825
00:44:09,120 --> 00:44:11,600
I asked my brother to help, but he didn’t.

826
00:44:12,230 --> 00:44:13,670
Annoying.
